HEADWORD: Guevi
<hw>Gue"vi</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One
of several very small species and varieties of African antelopes, of the
genus <gen>Cephalophus</gen>, as the Cape <ex>guevi</ex> or kleeneboc
(<spn>Cephalophus pygm⟦ae⟧a</spn>); -- called also <altname>pygmy
antelope</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

